value.value: 頭部の短縮
reduced anterior-posterior length of the head
頭部の動作異常
any anomaly in the motion of the portion of the body containing the brain and organs of sight, hearing, taste, and smell
引っ張られたような顔面
skin of face has appearance of being drawn or pulled tightly
頭蓋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the bones of the head
頭蓋の巨大化
increased size of the cranium
ドーム状の頭蓋
increased curvature to the hemispherical shape of the upper cranial case
頭蓋幅の増加
having an increased side-to-side, or lateral distance of the cranium
鼻の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions

definition.value: The term muzzle has multiple meanings and can be ambiguous. It has been added as a broad synonym, and in this case, refers both to the protruding part of the face seen in many animal species.

value.value: 鼻の短縮
reduced length of the anterior facial part of the muzzle
鼻の伸長
the anterior facial part of the muzzle having a length greater than seen in controls
平たい鼻
a snout flattened laterally along the whole length without the appearance of distinctive curvature
尖った鼻
muzzle tapers to a small tip, sharper angle than wild type
広い鼻梁
wider than normal upper part of the ridge of the nose
鼻の欠如
absence of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions
鱗状の鼻
loss of the outer layer of the epidermis of the muzzle in thick, dry scale-like patches
口の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the proximal portion of the digestive tract containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening
In vertebrates, the mouth extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these protrude from the mouth (tusks).
口の欠如
congenital absence of the mouth
顎の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the bony framework of the mouth where the teeth are held
上顎骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper bony framework of the mouth where the superior teeth are held
上顎骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the maxilla, typically resulting in decreased size
下顎骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the lower bony framework of the mouth where the inferior teeth are held
仙前椎の異常
any structural anomaly of the vertebrae anterior to the sacrum
下顎骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the mandible, typically resulting in decreased size
仙前椎数の減少
reduced number of the vertebrae anterior to the sacrum
消化器系の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the system dedicated to the mechanical, chemical, and enzymatic processing of food
仙前椎数の増加
greater number of the vertebrae anterior to the sacrum
消化管の出血
bleeding in the stomach and/or the intestines
食道上皮肥厚
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the esophageal epithelium, typically resulting in increased size
食道の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the part of the digestive canal through which food passes from the pharynx to the stomach
食道上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial layer that lines the luminal space of the esophagus
食道扁平上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the scaly epithelial layer of the esophagus
胃の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the hollow, sac-like structure of the digestive canal between the esophagus and the small intestine that functions to emulsify food
胃上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial layer of the stomach
胃扁平上皮の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the squamous epithelium that lines the distinct rodent non-glandular region of the stomach, i.e. the forestomach (aka anterior or proximal stomach); in neonatal and adult mice, this epithelium is stratified, fully keratinized, and devoid of gastric glands
胃腺上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the gland-containing epithelial layer of the stomach
前腸の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the anterior portion of the primitive digestive tube of the embryo that lies cephalic to the junction of the yolk stalk, consists of endodermal tissue, and gives rise to the pharynx, lower respiratory system, esophagus, stomach, duodenum proximal to the biliary tract, liver, pancreas, biliary tract, and gall bladder
腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the digestive tube passing from the stomach to the anus, consisting of the small and large intestine divisions
腸の発生遅延
slowed progression to a structurally mature intestine
腸細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial cells that have an apical plasma membrane folded into microvilli to provide ample surface for the absorption of nutrients from the intestinal lumen
肋骨数の増加
greater than normal numbers of the pairs of bony structures that are elements of the body wall
腸細胞数の異常
deviation from the normal numbers of enterocytes
腓骨の伸長
increased length of the lateral and smaller of bone of the lower leg
肺動脈の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the artery that arises from the right ventricle and conveys unaerated blood to the lungs
肺動脈幹の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the region of the pulmonary artery that arises from the right ventricle to the division of the right and left pulmonary artery
腸細胞の欠如
absence of the epithelial cells that have an apical plasma membrane folded into microvilli to provide ample surface for the absorption of nutrients from the intestinal lumen
腸管上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cellular avascular layer of the digestive tube passing from the stomach to the anus
大腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the digestive tube extending from the ileocecal valve to the anus, consisting of the cecum, colon, rectum and anal canal
リーベルキューン腺の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the tubular intestinal glands found in the mucosal membranes
リーベルキューン腺の膿瘍
an exudate collection associated with inflammation in the crypts of Lieberkuhn of the intestinal mucosa; often associated with ulcerative colitis
直腸の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the terminal portion of the intestinal tube adjacent to the anus
